  "instructions": [
    "Heat a skillet over medium-high and brown the lardons until crisp; set aside.",
    "In the same skillet add olive oil, diced onion, and minced garlic and cook until the onion softens.",
    "Stir in chopped tomatoes, cumin, coriander, paprika, and cayenne, and let the mixture simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Pour in Dutch stroop and squeeze in lemon juice, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Gently place the fish fillets on top of the sauce, cover, and bake in a preheated oven at 180°C for 12 minutes.",
    "Increase oven temperature to 200°C and bake for an additional 5 minutes until the fish flakes easily.",
    "Remove the tagine from the oven and garnish with chopped parsley before serving.",
    "Serve hot with a side of low-glycemic greens or a small portion of plain rice."
  ],
